<h2 id="get-started-45-minute-path">Get started (45-minute path)</h2>

<h3 id="1-install-mendeley-5-min">1. Install Mendeley (5 min)</h3>

<blockquote>
  <p><strong>Note:</strong> If you‚Äôre installing on workshop wifi alongside other participants, the download may take longer than expected. Flag Brady if you get stuck.</p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li>Go to <a href="https://www.mendeley.com/download-reference-manager/">mendeley.com/download-reference-manager</a> and install Mendeley Reference Manager (the desktop app)</li>
  <li>Install the <a href="https://www.mendeley.com/reference-management/web-importer">Mendeley Web Importer</a> browser extension</li>
  <li>Sign in or create a free account</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="2-add-sources-10-min">2. Add sources (10 min)</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Web Importer:</strong> Navigate to a journal article or book page and click the Mendeley Web Importer icon</li>
  <li><strong>DOI import:</strong> Click ‚ÄúAdd‚Äù ‚Üí ‚ÄúAdd entry manually‚Äù ‚Üí paste a DOI</li>
  <li><strong>Drag and drop:</strong> Drag a PDF directly into Mendeley ‚Äî it will try to extract metadata automatically (check for accuracy)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Exercise:</strong> Add 3‚Äì5 sources using different methods.</p>

<h3 id="3-organize-10-min">3. Organize (10 min)</h3>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Create folders:</strong> Right-click in the left panel ‚Üí ‚ÄúNew Folder‚Äù</li>
  <li><strong>Tag entries:</strong> Select a source, look for the ‚ÄúTags‚Äù field in the details panel</li>
  <li><strong>Star important items</strong> for quick access</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Exercise:</strong> Create 2 folders and organize your imported sources.</p>

<h3 id="4-annotate-pdfs-10-min">4. Annotate PDFs (10 min)</h3>

<p>Mendeley‚Äôs built-in PDF reader lets you highlight and annotate directly:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Open a PDF by double-clicking it</li>
  <li>Use the toolbar to highlight, add sticky notes, or underline</li>
  <li>Annotations are searchable and stay linked to the source</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Exercise:</strong> Open a PDF and add a few annotations.</p>

<h3 id="5-cite-in-a-document-10-min">5. Cite in a document (10 min)</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Install the Mendeley Cite plugin for Microsoft Word (look for it under Tools or in the Mendeley app settings)</li>
  <li>Open Word, find the Mendeley Cite tab</li>
  <li>Insert a citation, choose your style, and generate a bibliography</li>
</ul>

